By further expanding equation (6), the log-likelihood functions can be expressed as:


(7)
lnL=∑iN{di(−lnσ+ln∅(Yi−β1Xiσ))+(1−di)ln(1−∅(β1Xiσ))}

The equation (10) provided below can be utilized for MEs (ME-3) that rely solely on unfiltered observations of response variables:-


(10)
∂E[Yi|Yi〉0]∂Xi=βi{1−λ(α)[β1Xiσ+λ(α)]}
